{
  "stem": "214.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--and they that-- [INTERPOSING VOICES]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--because some of them have been running short, so he said you can-- he said go on over three--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, no so if she went 40 minutes, if somebody else goes over, it all kind of-- I think it will even itself out somewhere along the line.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My full name was [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hannah ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Zimmer ?] Lipszyc.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was born on the 27th of September, 1920, in the city of Lodz--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Poland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My married name is Anna Fischer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With-- with-- I-- I will tell you what was growing up for me, because, you know, there were-- as I say, I was born into a Hasidic-- I don't know if you know, maybe you heard about the [INAUDIBLE] called [INAUDIBLE], with one the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was a big-- and my-- my family-- my father's family-- was somehow related to them, and my cousin-- unfortunately, she's dying now, lives in Israel, who went to Palestine 1975.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, [INAUDIBLE] they got married.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She's always telling me, you don't know what a [YIDDISH] you are.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, you know what [YIDDISH] means?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What do you say, it was somebody in a very special, aristocratic, Hasidic family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because-- because [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Svasemesk ?], who was a great [INAUDIBLE] I don't know how many generations ago-- he was related to-- to my father, to my grandfather, to my great-grandfather, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Besides, I really didn't know my father's family so well, because they lived in Skierniewice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was born in Skierniewice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my-- my grandfather was still alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandmother died in the war in Skierniewice, because she was, in our eyes, she was a very old woman.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
